<summary>
## Summary: Milestone — Project Artifact Persistence

### Changes Implemented
- **`libs/types/src/project.ts`** — Added `ArtifactType`, `ArtifactIndexEntry`, `ArtifactIndex`, and `ProjectArtifact` type definitions
- **`apps/server/src/services/project-artifact-service.ts`** — Implemented `ProjectArtifactService` with `saveArtifact`, `listArtifacts`, and `getArtifact` methods backed by the filesystem
- **`apps/server/tests/unit/services/project-artifact-service.test.ts`** — 13 unit tests covering all three methods, index updates, directory creation, and type filtering
- **`apps/server/src/services/ceremony-service.ts`** — Wired in `ProjectArtifactService` via `setArtifactService()`; calls `saveArtifact` with `'ceremony-report'` on successful completion of both `milestone_retro` (retro flow) and `project_retro` (project retro flow)

### Files Modified
- `libs/types/src/project.ts` (modified — types added)
- `apps/server/src/services/project-artifact-service.ts` (new)
- `apps/server/tests/unit/services/project-artifact-service.test.ts` (new)
- `apps/server/src/services/ceremony-service.ts` (modified — artifact persistence wired in)

### Risks/Blockers Encountered
- None. All four files were already in place when the worktree was set up; the feature was complete and only needed verification.

### Learnings
- The `getProjectDir` helper from `@protolabsai/platform` already resolves `.automaker/projects/{slug}`, so the artifact paths naturally compose under it.
- The `CeremonyService` uses an optional `artifactService` setter pattern (dependency injection via `setArtifactService`) which keeps the service testable without requiring the artifact service.

### Notes for Developer
- The `ProjectArtifactService` singleton export (`projectArtifactService`) is ready to wire into `services.ts` in a follow-on integration step if needed.
- Artifact IDs are formatted as `{type}-{timestamp_ms}` (e.g. `ceremony-report-1709856127000`), making them human-readable and sortable.

### Verification Status
- **13/13 unit tests pass** for `ProjectArtifactService` covering save, list, get, index update, directory creation, and type filtering
- **`npm run build:server` exits with code 0** — full TypeScript compilation successful
- Playwright verification was not applicable — this feature is a pure backend service (file I/O + index management) with no UI surface
</summary>